 {"id":"bd-3bxhj.4","title":"epic(opentui-import): Translation engine and FrankenTUI code generation","description":"## Background
Translate canonical IR into idiomatic FrankenTUI code with high readability, predictable structure, and policy-aware fallback behavior.

## Scope
- Mapping atlas from IR constructs to FrankenTUI runtime/layout/widgets/style primitives.
- Confidence-ranked planner selecting exact/approximate/extend-ftui strategies.
- Code emission backend, project scaffolding, and optimization/readability passes.
- Unit tests for planner/templates and E2E translate-build ledger pipelines.

## Success Criteria
1. Generated projects compile/run deterministically for supported migration profiles.
2. Planner decisions are policy- and evidence-linked with explicit fallback semantics.
3. Emitted code quality (structure/readability) meets formatter/lint and template invariants.
4. Translate-and-build E2E scripts produce deterministic evidence ledgers.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:28:20.331961649Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-24T22:22:55.806108037Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["codegen","opentui-import","translation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.4","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:28:20.331961649Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
